## Roadmap — Prioritized

Priority logic: **Core training loop first** (every session benefits), then **data trust**, then **motivation/retention**, then **analytics**, then **big scope / future**.

---

### Tier 1 — Fix what's broken (do before anything else)
Small effort, high trust. These are bugs in already-built features.

| # | Item | Why first |
|---|---|---|
| 17a | Strength curve Y-axis + grid lines | Chart is misleading without it |
| 17b | Heatmap day-of-week labels | Can't read the calendar without them |
| 17c | Trophy count off-by-one | Wrong number in the header undermines trust |
| 17d | Stats Y-axis labels everywhere missing | Same — charts need scale |
| 17e | Heatmap legend + current-day marker | Basic readability |
| 17f | Better cardio weekly card (small chart) | Cardio section feels unfinished |
| 17g | Chart legends everywhere missing | Polish that makes existing data readable |

---

### Tier 2 — Core training loop (highest per-session impact)
These touch every single set of every single workout. Biggest ROI.

| # | Item | Effort | Why |
|---|---|---|---|
| 20 | Forgiving input parser ("45x10" as one string) | Small | Removes the biggest friction point in set logging |
| 19 | Quick-log "same as last set" (long-press set row) | Small | One tap instead of two fields — fast sets |
| 21 | Set autocomplete — typing reps suggests last weight | Small | Closes the "what did I do last time?" loop at input level |
| 13 | Weight suggestion on set entry based on last performance + difficulty rating | Medium | If you rated Hard on 25lb → suggest 22.5lb next time; the data is already in DB |
| 12 | Auto-progression rule ("hit top of rep range → +2.5lb next session") | Medium | Makes the app a real training partner, not a logbook |
| 24 | Single-tap "start last workout" — auto-fills all weights from last session | Medium | One button turns a blank screen into a pre-filled workout |

---

### Tier 3 — Rest timer + session UX
Timer is built but has one critical gap, and the session flow has quality-of-life holes.

| # | Item | Effort | Why |
|---|---|---|---|
| 16 | Push notification + vibration when rest timer finishes (screen off) | Small–Medium | Timer is useless if you pocket your phone mid-rest |
| 23 | Smart rest timer defaults per exercise type (compound 3min, isolation 90s) + +30s on Brutal rating | Small | The 2:30 flat default is wrong for most exercises |
| 26 | Haptic feedback on set logged + timer done | Small | Physical confirmation = fewer "did that save?" moments |
| 30 | PR celebration animation + trophy confetti | Small–Medium | PRs should feel like a moment, not a badge |
| 7 | Edit/delete logged sets + edit past sessions | Medium | Can't fix a mis-tap; this blocks trust in the data |

